-- Colombian Stock Movers: Avianca Taca Holding, Isagen Were Active
-- B y   B l a k e   S c h m i d t
-- 2012-03-01T22:04:06Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-01/colombian-stock-movers-avianca-taca-holding-isagen-were-active.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Bogota trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 4 p.m. local time.  The  IGBC Index (IGBC)  gained 1.6 percent to 15,169.74, while the
Colcap Index rose 0.6 percent to 1,740.64.  Avianca Taca Holding SA (PFAVTA)  (PFAVTA CB), the owner of
 Colombia ’s largest airline, fell 1.4 percent to 4,230 pesos.
Aeroperlas, the  Panama  City-based unit of Avianca Taca, ceased
operations in Panama, citing “the need to retool the airline’s
business model based on trend analysis and current market
conditions,” according to an e-mailed statement yesterday.  The 43-year-old company said it seeks to design a new model
of operations in the future, without giving further details. The
company said it had 113,222 passengers in 2011, a 2 percent
increase from the year before.  Avianca Taca said it will continue other international
flights to and from Panama City.  Isagen SA (ISAGEN)  , a Colombian energy company, gained
for a second day, rising 1.5 percent to 2,320 pesos.  “We emphasize the company’s good results and cash
generation,” analysts from Medellin-based brokerage Bolsa y
Renta, including Juan Camilo Martinez, said in an e-mailed
report yesterday. The brokerage maintained its “buy”
recommendation and year-end target price of 3,000 pesos.  The company said its 2011 profit rose 17 percent from the
year before to 479.1 billion pesos ($271 million), according to
a Feb. 27 regulatory filing. Four analysts surveyed by Bloomberg
had an average forecast of 425.1 billion pesos.  To contact the reporter on this story:
